   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "#3. Write a Python Program to Convert Decimal to Binary, Octal and Hexadecimal?"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "raw",
   "id": "42d68465",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "#By using the built-in functions bin, oct, and hex Decimal can be converted to Binary, Octal and Hexadecimal\n",
    "\n",
    "decimal = int(input(\"Enter a decimal number: \"))\n",
    "\n",
    "print(\"The binary representation of\", decimal, \"is\", bin(decimal))\n",
    "print(\"The octal representation of\", decimal, \"is\", oct(decimal))\n",
    "print(\"The hexadecimal representation of\", decimal, \"is\", hex(decimal))\n"
   ]
  },
